examples.en: This feeling gradually goes off.
Gradually the rain ceased.
We noticed a gradual change in temperature.
A pour of rain gradually turned to snow.
Gradually, my ankle got better.
You should gradually increase the duration of your workout.
His hard features gradually unbent.
The pain in his head gradually receded.
Gradually her anxiety lessened.
Gradually my soul began to unkink.
Gradually beat in the sugar.
The rumour gradually died a death.
Gradually I lost the courage to speak out about anything.
Gradually it percolated through to me.
His speech gradually became lighter in tone.
The hospital has made gradual improvements in health care.
The quantity of medicine to be taken can be stepped down gradually after the first week.
Gradually the mind was etherized to a dreamy placidity.
Exposure to rain and sun will gradually deteriorate the paint.
A flatness of mind was gradually stealing upon me.
Our talk gradually rounded into a plan for improving the organization.
The science of calculation by nine figures and zero was gradually superseding the abacus.
They gradually obliqued from the direct ascent.
The rambling of conversation gradually died down.
His theories gradually gained ground among academics.
He has gradually acquiesced to the demands of the opposition.
The inner layers of alburnum are gradually transformed into duramen.
The Siamese kittens are born absolutely white and gradually all the points come.
The rocks have gradually eroded away.
Her long illness was gradually sapping Charlotte's strength.
